==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[eradicatus]]'', the past participle of ''[[eradicare]]'', from ''[[e-#Latin|e-]]'', "out", + ''[[radix]]'' (root: ''[[radic-]]''), "root".

===Verb===
{{en-verb|eradicat|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[pull]] [[up]] by the [[root]]s; to [[root up]].
# {{transitive}} To [[completely]] [[destroy]]; to put an [[end]] to; to extirpate.

